# Pump Portable Shopify Theme Rules

You are editing a Shopify Online Store 2.0 theme.

## Do not treat this as React

Do not suggest:
- React components
- Next.js routing
- shadcn/ui
- TypeScript components
- client-side ecommerce state
- custom checkout

unless the user explicitly asks for Hydrogen/headless.

## Preserve Shopify Commerce Logic

Never casually remove or rewrite:
- product forms
- cart forms
- variant picker logic
- Shopify app blocks
- theme schemas
- Liquid objects
- dynamic checkout buttons
- localization/currency selectors
- customer account links
- structured data

## Editing Rules

When editing Liquid:

- preserve existing Shopify objects
- preserve schema settings
- preserve block support
- preserve app block rendering
- use semantic HTML
- avoid hardcoded product data
- avoid hardcoded URLs where Shopify routes exist
- avoid unnecessary JavaScript

## Design Direction

Pump Portable should feel:
- premium
- modern
- clean
- high-converting
- trustworthy
- mobile-first

Use strong sections:
- hero
- product benefits
- product showcase
- reviews
- comparison
- FAQ
- CTA

## Response Style

Before changing code, briefly state:
- what file you will edit
- what Shopify logic is protected
- what visual/UX improvement you are making

After changing code, state:
- changed files
- what to test in Shopify preview
